<inglise> COUNCIL DIRECTIVE 94/67/EC of 16 December 1994 on the incineration of hazardous waste </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 94/67/E&Uuml; ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letamise kohta 16. detsember 1994 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 103s (1) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 103s l&otilde;iget 1, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 189c of the Treaty (3), </inglise>
<eesti> toimides asutamislepingu artiklis 189c s&auml;testatud korras (3) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the objectives and principles of the Community's environment policy as set out in Article 130r of the Treaty, aim in particular at preventing pollution, rectifying pollution by acting as a priority at source, and applying the principle that the polluter should pay; </inglise>
<eesti> asutamislepingu artiklis 130r s&auml;testatud &uuml;henduse keskkonnapoliitika eesm&auml;rkide ja p&otilde;him&otilde;tetega p&uuml;&uuml;takse eelk&otilde;ige v&auml;ltida reostust, pannes r&otilde;hku selle v&auml;hendamisele tekkekohas ja kohaldades p&otilde;him&otilde;tet, et saastaja maksab; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Council resolution of 7 May 1990 on waste policy (4) invited the Commission to complete its proposals on incinerators for industrial waste, as a matter of urgency; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu 7. mai 1990. aasta resolutsioonis j&auml;&auml;tmepoliitika kohta (4) paluti komisjonil koostada kiiresti t&ouml;&ouml;stusj&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;leteid k&auml;sitlevad ettepanekud; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the incineration of hazardous waste gives rise to emissions which may cause pollution and thereby, unless properly controlled, harm human health and the environment; whereas in some cases there might be transboundary pollution; </inglise>
<eesti> ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letamisel tekivad heitmed, mis v&otilde;ivad p&otilde;hjustada reostust ja seel&auml;bi kahjustada inimeste tervist ja keskkonda, kui neid ei ohjata sobival viisil; m&otilde;nel juhul v&otilde;ib reostus olla piiri&uuml;lene; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas preventive action is therefore required to protect the environment against dangerous emissions from the incineration of hazardous waste; </inglise>
<eesti> seet&otilde;ttu on vaja ennetusmeetmeid, et kaitsta keskkonda ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letamisel tekkivate ohtlike heitmete eest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the current differences in national provisions applicable to the incineration of hazardous waste, and in some cases the absence of such provisions, justify action at Community level; </inglise>
<eesti> ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letamist k&auml;sitlevate siseriiklike &otilde;igusnormide praegused erinevused ja m&otilde;nel juhul nende normide puudumine &otilde;igustavad meetmete v&otilde;tmist &uuml;henduse tasandil; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in accordance with Article 130t of the Treaty, the adoption of this Directive will not prevent any Member State from maintaining or introducing more stringent measures for the protection of the environment compatible with the Treaty; </inglise>
<eesti> asutamislepingu artikli 130t kohaselt ei takista k&auml;esoleva direktiivi vastuv&otilde;tmine &uuml;htki liikmesriiki s&auml;ilitamast v&otilde;i kehtestamast rangemaid keskkonnakaitsemeetmeid, kui need on koosk&otilde;las asutamislepinguga; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 4 of Council Directive 75/442/EEC of 15 July 1975 on waste (5), requires Member States to take the necessary measures to ensure that waste is recovered or disposed of without endangering human health and without harming the environment; whereas, to this end, Article 9 of that Directive stipulates that any installation or undertaking treating waste must obtain a permit from the competent authorities relating, inter alia, to the precautions to be taken; </inglise>
<eesti> j&auml;&auml;tmeid k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 15. juuli 1975. aasta direktiivi 75/442/EM&Uuml; (5) artikkel 4 kohustab liikmesriike v&otilde;tma vajalikke meetmeid tagamaks, et j&auml;&auml;tmeid taaskasutatakse v&otilde;i need k&otilde;rvaldatakse nii, et see ei ohustaks inimeste tervist ega kahjustaks keskkonda; selleks s&auml;testatakse k&otilde;nealuse direktiivi artiklis 9, et iga j&auml;&auml;tmeid t&ouml;&ouml;tlev k&auml;itis v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tja peab saama p&auml;devatelt asutustelt loa, mis muu hulgas k&auml;sitleb v&otilde;etavaid ettevaatusabin&otilde;usid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Articles 3 and 4 of Council Directive 84/360/EEC of 28 June 1984 on the combating of air pollution from industrial plants (6), provide that prior authorization shall be required for the operation of industrial plants belonging to listed categories among which are waste incineration plants; </inglise>
<eesti> t&ouml;&ouml;stusrajatistest l&auml;htuva &otilde;husaaste vastu v&otilde;itlemist k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 28. juuni 1984. aasta direktiivi 84/360/EM&Uuml; (6) artiklites 3 ja 4 s&auml;testatakse, et loetletud liikidesse kuuluvate t&ouml;&ouml;stusrajatiste, sealhulgas j&auml;&auml;tmep&otilde;letusrajatiste k&auml;itamiseks on vaja eelnevat luba; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the purpose of the incineration plants established and operated under this Directive is to reduce the pollution-related risks of hazardous waste through a process of oxidation, to reduce the quantity and volume of the waste and to produce residues that can be re-used or diposed of safely; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva direktiivi alusel rajatavate ja k&auml;itatavate p&otilde;letusrajatiste eesm&auml;rk on v&auml;hendada ohtlikest j&auml;&auml;tmetest tulenevat reostusohtu oks&uuml;datsiooni abil, v&auml;hendada j&auml;&auml;tmete kogust ja toota j&auml;&auml;ke, mida saab uuesti kasutada v&otilde;i ohutult k&otilde;rvaldada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas a high level of environmental protection requires the setting and maintaining of appropriate operating conditions and emission limit values for hazardous waste incineration plants within the Community; whereas special provisions are necessary in the case of emissions of dioxins and furans which it is essential to reduce by using the most progressive technology; </inglise>
<eesti> heatasemeline keskkonnakaitse eeldab sobivate k&auml;itamistingimuste ja heitmete piirv&auml;&auml;rtuste kehtestamist ja s&auml;ilitamist &uuml;henduses asuvate ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letusrajatiste suhtes; eris&auml;tteid on vaja dioksiinide ja furaanide heitmete kohta, mille v&auml;hendamiseks tuleks kasutada arenenuimat tehnoloogiat; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas high-standard measurement techniques are required to monitor emissions to ensure compliance with the emission limit and guide values for the pollutants; </inglise>
<eesti> heitmete j&auml;lgimiseks on vaja heatasemelisi m&otilde;&otilde;tmisv&otilde;tteid, et tagada saasteainete heitmete piir- ja suunisv&auml;&auml;rtustest kinnipidamine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas integrated protection of the environment against emissions resulting from the incineration of hazardous waste is required; whereas, therefore, aqueous waste resulting from the cleaning of exhaust gases may be discharged after separate treatment only, in order to limit a transfer of pollution from one environmental medium to another; whereas specific emission limit values for pollutants in such aqueous waste should be established within two years of the date of entry into force of this Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letamisel tekkivate heitmete eest on keskkonda vaja kaitsta terviklikult; seet&otilde;ttu v&otilde;ib heitgaaside puhastamisel tekkivaid veesisaldusega j&auml;&auml;tmeid v&auml;ljutada &uuml;ksnes p&auml;rast erit&ouml;&ouml;tlust, et v&auml;hendada reostuse sattumist &uuml;hest keskkonnast teise; sellistes veesisaldusega j&auml;&auml;tmetes olevate saasteainete heitmetele tuleks kehtestada eraldi piirv&auml;&auml;rtused kahe aasta jooksul k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&otilde;ustumisest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas provisions should be laid down for cases where the emission limit values are exceeded as well as for technically unavoidable stoppages, disturbances or failures of the purification devices; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks kehtestada s&auml;tted juhtudeks, mil heitmete piirv&auml;&auml;rtusi &uuml;letatakse, samuti puhastusseadmete tehniliselt v&auml;ltimatute seisakute, h&auml;irete v&otilde;i rikete puhuks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the coincineration of hazardous waste in plants not primarily intended to incinerate hazardous waste should not be allowed to cause higher emissions of polluting substances in that part of the exhaust gas volume resulting from such coincineration and should therefore be subject to appropriate limitations; </inglise>
<eesti> ei tohiks lubada, et ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete koosp&otilde;letamine rajatistes, mis ei ole m&otilde;eldud eesk&auml;tt ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letamiseks, p&otilde;hjustab suuremaid saasteainete heitmeid heitgaaside osas, mis tekib sellisest koosp&otilde;letamisest, mist&otilde;ttu k&otilde;nealust koosp&otilde;letamist tuleks asjakohaselt piirata; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for better protection of human health and the environment, rapid adaptation of existing incineration plants to the emission limit values laid down in this Directive is required so as to avoid an increased transfer of hazardous wastes to such plants; </inglise>
<eesti> inimeste tervise ja keskkonna paremaks kaitsmiseks on olemasolevad p&otilde;letusrajatised vaja kiiresti kohandada k&auml;esolevas direktiivis s&auml;testatud heitmete piirv&auml;&auml;rtustega, et v&auml;ltida nendesse rajatistesse viidatavate ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete koguse suurenemist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas a committee should be set up to assist the Commission in implementing this Directive and adapting it to scientific and technical progress; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks asutada komitee, kes abistaks komisjoni k&auml;esoleva direktiivi rakendamisel ja kohandamisel teaduse ja tehnika edusammudega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the reports on the implementation of this Directive are an important element for informing the Commission and Member States on the progress achieved in emission control techniques; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva direktiivi rakendamist k&auml;sitlevad aruanded on oluline vahend, millega komisjoni ja liikmesriike teavitatakse heitmeohjev&otilde;tete vallas tehtud edusammudest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas proposals for the revision of the emission limit values and related provisions of this Directive should be submitted to the Council before 31 December 2000 in the light of the expected development of the state of technology, of experience in the operation of incineration plants and of environmental requirements, </inglise>
<eesti> ettepanekud heitmete piirv&auml;&auml;rtuste ja k&auml;esoleva direktiivi asjakohaste s&auml;tete l&auml;bivaatamiseks tuleks n&otilde;ukogule esitada enne 31. detsembrit 2000, pidades silmas tehnoloogia eeldatavat arengut, kogemusi p&otilde;letusrajatiste k&auml;itamisel ja keskkonnan&otilde;udeid, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The aim of this Directive is to provide for measures and procedures to prevent or, where that is not practicable, to reduce as fas as possible negative effects on the environment, in particular the pollution of air, soil, surface and groundwater, and the resulting risks to human health, from the incineration of hazardous waste and, to that end, to set up and maintain appropriate operating conditions and emission limit values for hazardous waste incineration plants within the Community. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on n&auml;ha ette meetmed ja menetlused, et v&auml;ltida v&otilde;i, kui see ei ole v&otilde;imalik, v&auml;hendada v&otilde;imaluse piires ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letamisest tulenevat kahjulikku m&otilde;ju keskkonnale, eelk&otilde;ige &otilde;hu, pinnase ja pinna- ja p&otilde;hjavee saastumist ning sellest tulenevaid ohte inimeste tervisele, ning selleks kehtestada ja s&auml;ilitada &uuml;henduses asuvate ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letusrajatiste suhtes k&auml;itamistingimused ja heitmete piirv&auml;&auml;rtused. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive applies without prejudice to other relevant Community legislation, in particular relating to waste and the protection of the health and safety of workers at incineration plants. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamine ei piira kohaldamast muid asjakohaseid &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusnorme, mis k&auml;sitlevad eelk&otilde;ige j&auml;&auml;tmeid ja p&otilde;letusrajatiste t&ouml;&ouml;kaitset. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. 'hazardous waste' means any solid or liquid waste as defined in Article 1 (4) of Council Directive 91/689/EEC of 12 December 1991 on hazardous waste (1). </inglise>
<eesti> 1) ohtlikud j&auml;&auml;tmed - mis tahes tahked v&otilde;i vedelad j&auml;&auml;tmed, nagu on m&auml;&auml;ratletud ohtlikke j&auml;&auml;tmeid k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 12. detsembri 1991. aasta direktiivi 91/689/EM&Uuml; (7) artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The following hazardous wastes shall however be excluded from the scope of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamisalast on siiski v&auml;lja arvatud j&auml;rgmised ohtlikud j&auml;&auml;tmed: </eesti>
<inglise> - combustible liquid wastes including waste oils as defined in Article 1 of Council Directive 75/439/EEC of 16 June 1975 on the disposal of waste oils (2) provided that they meet the following three criteria: </inglise>
<eesti> - p&otilde;levad vedelad j&auml;&auml;tmed, sealhulgas &otilde;lij&auml;&auml;tmete k&otilde;rvaldamist k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 16. juuni 1975. aasta direktiivi 75/439/EM&Uuml; (8) artiklis 1 m&auml;&auml;ratletud &otilde;lij&auml;&auml;tmed, juhul kui need vastavad j&auml;rgmisele kolmele tingimusele: </eesti>
<inglise> (i) the mass content of polychlorinated aromatic hydrocarbons, e.g. polychlorinated biphenyls (PCB) or pentachlorinated phenol (PCP), amounts to concentrations not higher than those set out in the relevant Community legislation; </inglise>
<eesti> i) pol&uuml;klooritud aromaatsete s&uuml;sivesinike, n&auml;iteks pol&uuml;klooritud difen&uuml;&uuml;lide (PCB) v&otilde;i pentaklooritud fenooli (PCP) sisaldus massi j&auml;rgi ei ole suurem, kui asjakohastes &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusnormides on s&auml;testatud, </eesti>
<inglise> (ii) these wastes are not rendered hazardous by virtue of containing other constituents listed in Annex II to Directive 91/689/EEC in quantities or in concentrations which are inconsistent with the achievement of the objectives set out in Article 4 of Directive 75/442/EEC; and (iii) the net calorific value amounts to at least 30 MJ per kilogramme, </inglise>
<eesti> ii) neid j&auml;&auml;tmeid ei peeta ohtlikuks p&otilde;hjusel, et nendes sisalduvate muude direktiivi 91/689/EM&Uuml; II lisas loetletud koostisainete kogused v&otilde;i sisaldused on sellised, mis on direktiivi 75/442/EM&Uuml; artiklis 4 s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rkide saavutamisega vastuolus, ja iii) v&auml;ikseim k&uuml;ttev&auml;&auml;rtus on v&auml;hemalt 30 MJ/kg; </eesti>
<inglise> - any combustible liquid wastes which cannot cause, in the flue gas directly resulting from their combustion, emissions other than those from gasoil as defined in Article 1 (1) of Directive 75/716/EEC (3) or a higher concentration of emissions than those resulting from the combustion of gasoil as so defined, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&otilde;ik p&otilde;levad vedelad j&auml;&auml;tmed, mille p&otilde;lemisel vahetult tekkivad suitsugaasid ei p&otilde;hjusta muid heitmeid v&otilde;i suurema saasteainesisaldusega heitmeid kui need, mis tekivad direktiivi 75/716/EM&Uuml; (9) artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 m&auml;&auml;ratletud gaasi&otilde;li p&otilde;lemisel; </eesti>
<inglise> - hazardous waste resulting from the exploration for and the exploitation of oil and gas resources from off-shore installations and incinerated on board, </inglise>
<eesti> - ohtlikud j&auml;&auml;tmed, mis tekivad nafta ja gaasi otsimisel ja kasutamisel avamererajatistes ja mis p&otilde;letatakse seal; </eesti>
<inglise> - municipal waste covered by Directives 89/369/EEC (1) and 89/429/EEC (2), </inglise>
<eesti> - direktiividega 89/369/EM&Uuml; (10) ja 89/429/EM&Uuml; (11) h&otilde;lmatud olmej&auml;&auml;tmed; </eesti>
<inglise> - sewage sludges from the treatment of municipal waste waters which are not rendered hazardous by virtue of containing constituents listed in Annex II to Directive 91/689/EEC in quantities or in concentrations, as defined by the Member States until the list of hazardous wastes referred to in Article 1 (4) of that Directive is established, which are inconsistent with the achievement of the objectives set out in Article 4 of Directive 75/442/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> - olmeheitvee t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisel tekkivad setted, mida ei peeta ohtlikuks p&otilde;hjusel, et nendes sisalduvate, direktiivi 91/689/EM&Uuml; II lisas loetletud koostisainete kogused v&otilde;i sisaldused, nagu liikmesriigid on need m&auml;&auml;ratlenud k&otilde;nealuse direktiivi artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 4 osutatud ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete loendi kehtestamiseni, on sellised, mis on direktiivi 75/442/EM&Uuml; artiklis 4 s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rkide saavutamisega vastuolus. </eesti>
<inglise> This exlusion is without prejudice to Directive 86/278/EEC (3); </inglise>
<eesti> See v&auml;ljaarvamine ei piira direktiivi 86/278/EM&Uuml; (12) kohaldamist; </eesti>
<inglise> 2. 'incineration plant' means any technical equipment used for the incineration by oxidation of hazardous wastes with or without recovery of the combustion heat generated, including pretreatment as well as pyrolysis or other thermal treatment processes, e. g. plasma process, insofar as their products are subsequently incinerated. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) p&otilde;letusrajatis - mis tahes tehniline varustus, mida kasutatakse ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letamiseks oks&uuml;deerimise teel, olenemata sellest, kas p&otilde;lemisel tekkiv soojus kasutatakse &auml;ra v&otilde;i mitte, sealhulgas eelt&ouml;&ouml;tluseks v&otilde;i utmiseks v&otilde;i muuks soojust&ouml;&ouml;tluseks, n&auml;iteks plasmat&ouml;&ouml;tluseks, kuiv&otilde;rd saadavad tooted seej&auml;rel p&otilde;letatakse. </eesti>
<inglise> This includes plants burning such wastes as a regular or additional fuel for any industrial process. </inglise>
<eesti> See h&otilde;lmab rajatisi, kus selliseid j&auml;&auml;tmeid p&otilde;letatakse mis tahes t&ouml;&ouml;stusliku menetluse p&otilde;hi- v&otilde;i lisak&uuml;tusena. </eesti>
<inglise> This definition covers the site and the entire installation comprising the waste reception, storage and pretreatment facilities, the incinerator, its wastes, fuel and air-supply systems, exhaust gas and waste water treatment facilities, and devices and systems for controlling incineration operations and continuously recording and monitoring incineration conditions. </inglise>
<eesti> See m&otilde;iste h&otilde;lmab tegevuskohta ja kogu rajatist, sealhulgas j&auml;&auml;tmete vastuv&otilde;tu-, s&auml;ilitus- ja eelt&ouml;&ouml;tlusseadmeid, p&otilde;letit ja selle j&auml;&auml;tmeid, k&uuml;tuse- ja &otilde;huvarustuss&uuml;steeme, heitgaaside ja -vee t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisseadmeid ning seadmeid ja s&uuml;steeme p&otilde;letamise juhtimiseks ja p&otilde;letustingimuste pidevaks &uuml;lesm&auml;rkimiseks ja j&auml;lgimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> The following plants are not covered by this definition: </inglise>
<eesti> See m&otilde;iste ei h&otilde;lma j&auml;rgmisi rajatisi: </eesti>
<inglise> - incinerators for animal carcases or remains, </inglise>
<eesti> - loomakorjuste v&otilde;i -j&auml;&auml;nuste p&otilde;letid; </eesti>
<inglise> - incinerators for infectious clinical waste provided that such waste is not rendered hazardous as a result of the presence of other constituents listed in Annex II to Directive 91/689/EEC, or - municipal waste incinerators also burning infectious clinical waste which is not mixed with other wastes which are rendered hazardous as a result of one of the other properties listed in Annex III to Directive 91/689/EEC; </inglise>
<eesti> - nakkusohtlike haiglaj&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letid, tingimusel et selliseid j&auml;&auml;tmeid ei peeta ohtlikuks p&otilde;hjusel, et need sisaldavad muid direktiivi 91/689/EM&Uuml; II lisas loetletud koostisaineid; v&otilde;i - olmej&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letid, kus p&otilde;letatakse ka nakkusohtlikke haiglaj&auml;&auml;tmeid, mis ei ole segatud muude j&auml;&auml;tmetega, mida peetakse ohtlikuks m&otilde;ne muu direktiivi 91/689/EM&Uuml; III lisas loetletud omaduse t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise> 3. 'new incineration plant' means a plant for which the permit to operate is granted on or after the date specified in Article 18 (1); </inglise>
<eesti> 3) uus p&otilde;letusrajatis - rajatis, mille k&auml;itamisluba on antud artikli 18 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud kuup&auml;eval v&otilde;i hiljem; </eesti>
<inglise> 4. 'existing incineration plant' means a plant for which the original permit to operate is granted before the date specified in Article 18 (1); </inglise>
<eesti> 4) olemasolev p&otilde;letusrajatis - rajatis, mille esialgne k&auml;itamisluba on antud enne artikli 18 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud kuup&auml;eva; </eesti>
<inglise> 5. 'emission limit value' means the mass concentration of polluting substances which is not to be exceeded in emissions from plants during a specified period; </inglise>
