<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> All incineration plants shall be designed, equipped and operated in such a way that the gas resulting from the incineration of the hazardous waste is raised, after the last injection of combustion air, in a controlled and homogeneous fashion and even under the most unfavourable conditions anticipated, to a temperature of at least 850 &deg;C, as achieved at or near the inner wall of the combustion chamber, for at least two seconds in the presence of at least 6 % oxygen; if hazardous wastes with a content of more than 1 % of halogenated organic substances, expressed as chlorine, are incinerated, the temperature has to be raised to at least 1 100 &deg;C. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;ik p&otilde;letusrajatised kavandatakse, varustatakse ja k&auml;itatakse nii, et ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letamisel tekkiv gaas kuumeneb p&auml;rast viimast p&otilde;lemis&otilde;hu etteannet juhitavalt ja &uuml;htlaselt isegi v&otilde;imalikult ebasoodsates tingimustes v&auml;hemalt kaheks sekundiks v&auml;hemalt temperatuurini 850&deg;C p&otilde;lemiskambri siseseina juures v&otilde;i selle l&auml;hedal, kusjuures hapnikku on v&auml;hemalt 6%; selliste ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete p&otilde;letamisel, mis sisaldavad kloorina v&auml;ljendatud halogeenitud orgaanilisi aineid &uuml;le 1%, peab saavutatav temperatuur olema v&auml;hemalt 1100&deg;C. </eesti>
<inglise> When the furnace is fuelled with liquid hazardous waste only or with a mixture of gaseous substances and powdered solids from a thermal pretreatment of hazardous waste under oxygen deficiency, and when the gaseous part accounts for more than 50 % of the entire heat released, the oxygen content after the last injection of combustion air shall amout to at least 3 %. </inglise>
